# Apex Framework — Project Rules (BigCommerce / Catalyst)

This project uses the Apex agentic framework adapted for BigCommerce headless storefronts on Catalyst (Next.js App Router). Honour the following at every turn.

## Decision Priority
1. User-provided input (designs, references, requirements)
2. Project context and stack context in `CLAUDE.md`
3. Project code standards in `.claude/rules/code-standards.md`
4. Existing codebase patterns
5. Framework best practices as a last resort

## SDLC
Plan → Implement → Build → Review → Test → Deploy → Validate

- Complete each phase before the next. Do not skip or merge.
- After writing code, run the build immediately.
- Status line per phase transition; no summaries or permission requests between phases.
- S/M complexity execute autonomously end-to-end. L tasks ask before Deploy only.

## Agent Roster
- `planner` — implementation planning, task classification, complexity sizing
- `solutions-architect` — single-recommendation architectural decisions
- `backend-dev` — server actions, route handlers, GraphQL queries, REST integrations, webhooks, customer auth, B2B
- `frontend-dev` — RSC + client components, Tailwind, Makeswift, accessibility
- `code-reviewer` — multi-lens review with autonomous fixes
- `junits-specialist` — Vitest + RTL + MSW unit/integration tests
- `validation-tester` — post-deploy validation (Chrome DevTools / Playwright)
- `research-intelligence` — authoritative doc lookup (BC, Catalyst, Next.js, Makeswift)
- `code-explorer` — codebase scan for reuse and convention fingerprinting
- `functional-pmo` — backlog management (ADO/Jira via MCP)
- `docs-scribe` — documentation
- `bulk-bug-fixer` — multi-ticket bug analysis orchestrator

## Skills (load on demand)
- `bigcommerce-standards` — Catalyst, GraphQL Storefront, REST Management, B2B, Makeswift, webhooks, testing
- `frontend-code-standards` — React/Next.js/Tailwind standards
- `planning-standards` — task classification, implementation contracts, deployment planning
- `bugfix-workflow` — single-ticket and bulk bug procedures
- `figma-context`, `live-site-context`, `storybook-patterns`, `story-context` — input extractors
- `initialize-setup` — populate CLAUDE.md sections from architect doc or codebase scan
- `framework-guidance`, `skill-creator`, `skill-review` — framework maintenance

## Delegation
- Codebase discovery → `code-explorer`
- External docs / API references → `research-intelligence`
- Domain work → the specialist that owns it; the coordinator does not execute

## Boundaries
- Do not create agents, skills, commands, or hooks unless asked
- Do not add dependencies unless asked
- Confirm before destructive changes
- Work within what exists

## Security Defaults
- Never expose `BIGCOMMERCE_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `AUTH_SECRET`, customer impersonation token, `B2B_API_TOKEN`, or `MAKESWIFT_SITE_API_KEY` to the browser bundle
- Verify every webhook signature with `crypto.timingSafeEqual`
- Validate every server action input with Zod
- `cache: 'no-store'` for customer, cart, and order queries
